Package io.artframework.annotations

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    ART
    Every art object and module needs an ART annotation to provide the identifier and mark it as an art object.
    ArtModule
    This annotation marks the given class as an art module and provides additional meta data for it.
    Config
    This annotation makes it possible to load your configuration from a file.
    ConfigOption
    Provides meta information about configurable fields in a class to the ConfigMap.
    Ignore
    Ignores the given field as a config value and does not parse it.
    OnBootstrap
    Marks the given method as the bootstrap method for an art module.
    OnDisable
    Marks the given method as the disable method for an art module.
    OnEnable
    Marks the given method as the enable method for an art module.
    OnLoad
    Marks the given method as the load method for an art module.
    OnReload
    Marks the given method as the reload method for an art module.
    Resolve
    Marks the config field type as to be resolved using a Resolver.
